  "poem": {
    "content": "The floorboards creaked, a brisk wind blew,\nUnder a fence, shadows grew.\nThe crew assembled, a motley sight,\nTheir task: to navigate the fading light.\n\nNo toast tonight, no laughter's cheer,\nOnly the negative whispers, sharp and clear.\nOnce, a craft sailed free and bold,\nNow, its story tarnished, growing cold.\n\nThe chef has fled, his spices gone,\nLeaving a barrel empty, hope withdrawn.\nA sample taken, a bitter taste,\nUpon the plate, a future misplaced.\n\nThe lounge stands empty, still and deep,\nWhere broken dreams their secrets keep.\nNo second chance, the die is cast,\nThe future buried, fading fast.\nA broken craft, now beyond repair.\n\nNow under the fence, a burden to bear.",
